trans-unit.source: Authorization
trans-unit.target: Authorization

trans-unit.source: Only the account owner may call this operation.
trans-unit.target: Only the account owner may call this operation.

trans-unit.source: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation writes a range of byte to a file.
trans-unit.target: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation writes a range of byte to a file.

trans-unit.source: This operation can only be called on an existing file.
trans-unit.target: This operation can only be called on an existing file.

trans-unit.source: It cannot be called to create a new file.
trans-unit.target: It cannot be called to create a new file.

trans-unit.source: Calling <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> with a file name that does not currently exist returns status code 404 (Not Found).
trans-unit.target: Calling <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> with a file name that does not currently exist returns status code 404 (Not Found).

trans-unit.source: To create a new file, call <link xlink:href="211d8e61-05b5-420d-bd4b-8cee40e0c3de" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Create File</link>.
trans-unit.target: To create a new file, call <link xlink:href="211d8e61-05b5-420d-bd4b-8cee40e0c3de" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Create File</link>.

trans-unit.source: A file may be up to 1 TB in size.
trans-unit.target: A file may be up to 1 TB in size.

trans-unit.source: A <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation is permitted 10 minutes per MB to complete.
trans-unit.target: A <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation is permitted 10 minutes per MB to complete.

trans-unit.source: If the operation is taking longer than 10 minutes per MB on average, the operation will timeout.
trans-unit.target: If the operation is taking longer than 10 minutes per MB on average, the operation will timeout.

trans-unit.source: Range Update Operations
trans-unit.target: Range Update Operations

trans-unit.source: Calling <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> with the <parameterReference>Update</parameterReference> option performs an in-place write on the specified file.
trans-unit.target: Calling <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> with the <parameterReference>Update</parameterReference> option performs an in-place write on the specified file.

trans-unit.source: Any content in the specified range is overwritten with the update.
trans-unit.target: Any content in the specified range is overwritten with the update.

trans-unit.source: Each range submitted with <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> for an update operation may be up to 4 MB in size.
trans-unit.target: Each range submitted with <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> for an update operation may be up to 4 MB in size.

trans-unit.source: If you attempt to upload a range that is larger than 4 MB, the service returns status code 413 (Request Entity Too Large).
trans-unit.target: If you attempt to upload a range that is larger than 4 MB, the service returns status code 413 (Request Entity Too Large).

trans-unit.source: Range Clear Operations
trans-unit.target: Range Clear Operations

trans-unit.source: Calling <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> with the <parameterReference>Clear</parameterReference> option releases the space in storage as long as the specified range is 512-byte aligned.
trans-unit.target: Calling <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> with the <parameterReference>Clear</parameterReference> option releases the space in storage as long as the specified range is 512-byte aligned.

trans-unit.source: Ranges that have been cleared are no longer tracked as part of the file and will not be returned in the <link xlink:href="9645eb34-6ff8-41c3-a3bb-46bac44171ea" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">List Ranges</link> response.
trans-unit.target: Ranges that have been cleared are no longer tracked as part of the file and will not be returned in the <link xlink:href="9645eb34-6ff8-41c3-a3bb-46bac44171ea" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">List Ranges</link> response.

trans-unit.source: If the specified range is not 512-byte aligned, the operation will write zeros to the start or end of the range that is not 512-byte aligned and free the rest of the range inside that is 512-byte aligned.
trans-unit.target: If the specified range is not 512-byte aligned, the operation will write zeros to the start or end of the range that is not 512-byte aligned and free the rest of the range inside that is 512-byte aligned.

trans-unit.source: Any ranges that have not been cleared will be returned in the <link xlink:href="9645eb34-6ff8-41c3-a3bb-46bac44171ea" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">List Ranges</link> response.
trans-unit.target: Any ranges that have not been cleared will be returned in the <link xlink:href="9645eb34-6ff8-41c3-a3bb-46bac44171ea" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">List Ranges</link> response.

trans-unit.source: For an example, see <embeddedLabel>Sample Unaligned Clear Range</embeddedLabel> below.
trans-unit.target: For an example, see <embeddedLabel>Sample Unaligned Clear Range</embeddedLabel> below.

trans-unit.source: SMB Client Byte Range Locks
trans-unit.target: SMB Client Byte Range Locks

trans-unit.source: While the SMB protocol allows byte range locks to manage read and write access to regions of a file, the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation does not leverage this capability for the specified <parameterReference>x-ms-range</parameterReference> value.
trans-unit.target: While the SMB protocol allows byte range locks to manage read and write access to regions of a file, the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation does not leverage this capability for the specified <parameterReference>x-ms-range</parameterReference> value.

trans-unit.source: Instead, <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> requires write access to the entire file.
trans-unit.target: Instead, <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> requires write access to the entire file.

trans-unit.source: This also means that <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> will fail if an SMB client has a lock on any range within the file.
trans-unit.target: This also means that <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Put Range</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> will fail if an SMB client has a lock on any range within the file.

trans-unit.source: For more details, see <link xlink:href="06db1069-ee35-4410-9b56-31c40a2cd276" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Managing File Locks</link>.
trans-unit.target: For more details, see <link xlink:href="06db1069-ee35-4410-9b56-31c40a2cd276" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Managing File Locks</link>.

trans-unit.source: SMB Client Directory Change Notifications
trans-unit.target: SMB Client Directory Change Notifications

trans-unit.source: The SMB protocol supports the <link xlink:href="msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/aa364417.aspx" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">FindFirstChangeNotification</link> API function that allows applications to detect when changes occur in the file system.
trans-unit.target: The SMB protocol supports the <link xlink:href="msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/desktop/aa364417.aspx" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">FindFirstChangeNotification</link> API function that allows applications to detect when changes occur in the file system.

trans-unit.source: It can detect when a file or directory is added, changed, deleted, and when a file’s size, attributes, or security descriptors change.
trans-unit.target: It can detect when a file or directory is added, changed, deleted, and when a file’s size, attributes, or security descriptors change.

trans-unit.source: SMB clients using this API will not receive notifications when a file or directory change happens via the File service REST API.
trans-unit.target: SMB clients using this API will not receive notifications when a file or directory change happens via the File service REST API.

trans-unit.source: However, changes caused by other SMB clients will propagate notifications.
trans-unit.target: However, changes caused by other SMB clients will propagate notifications.
